@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'SevenHex' where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed.

                             How to play?

  SevenHex is played on an hexagonally shaped board which contains a
number of spaces that are joined by lines that connect them horizontally
or diagonally. The goal is to place 7 pawns so that none of them are in
line with each other.

  You play by clicking on an empty space where you want to place a pawn,
and a shape will appear there. If there are other pawns in line, either
horizontally or diagonally from that space, they will be removed from
the board.

  A display, on the lower right in the window, shows how many pawns are
placed on the board as well as the actual total to place. When those
numbers are equal,the game is completed.

  You can restart a game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub} button.

  Have fun!

@endnode

